Job Description 
Takes full responsibility for monthly closing of all US related entities 
Analyzes and reports financial data to local & group management 
In charge of collecting, processing and delivering relevant, timely and accurate accounting information within a global workflow 
Manages and works on general accounting tasks and actively organize local audits in the US 
Local business partner for global Group Accounting to ensure proper coverage of all accounting procedures 
Point of contact regarding basic accounting topics for local top management and all local business departments like legal, HR, etc. 
Supports and actively participates in international projects 
Qualifications 
University degree in business administration with a focus on accounting 
At least 3-5 years of experience in a similar role 
Professional certification in accounting or finance preferred 
Hands-on mentality 
Excellent knowledge of MS-Office (especially Excel) 
Technical experience with accounting software advantageous, especially Microsoft Dynamics and Tagetik 
Excellent accounting and analytic skills 
Personal responsibility, ability to work independently and against timelines, and enjoys changes and innovations 
Someone who strives for career development and growth opportunities on an international team 
The drive and interest to get to know the most successful young German tech company while growing with us! 
Additional Information 
Teams that collaborate and work with each other towards a common goal 
